OL,3,C'He'd be very proud': Family of Hector
OL,4,CDuff mark 80th anniversary of D-Day
OL,6,FHis grandson, Stephen Hall, said: "I
OL,7,Fthink he'd be very proud and very
OL,8,Fhumbled by what's going on".
OL,10,F"He would have loved to have been part
OL,11,Fof it, he would loved to have gone to
OL,12,Fthe new memorial (in Normandy)."
OL,14,FHector Duff landed on the beaches in
OL,15,FNormandy on 6 June 1944.
OL,17,FHe served with both the 7th Armoured
OL,18,FDivision in North Africa, and the
OL,19,FRoyal Tank Regiment - part of the 50th
OL,20,FBritish Division which landed on Gold
OL,21,Fbeach in Normandy in 1944.
