OL,3,C'He'd be very proud': Family of Hector
OL,4,CDuff mark 80th anniversary of D-Day
OL,6,FIn March 2020, aged 100, he was
OL,7,Fawarded an OBE - making him the oldest
OL,8,Frecipient in the New Year's Honours
OL,9,Flist.
OL,11,FIn his later life, he spent many years
OL,12,Ftelling stories of his time on war,
OL,13,Fwhile also looking after many of the
OL,14,Fmemorials around the Isle of Man.
OL,16,FHis grandson Stephen added: "He was
OL,17,Falways trying to teach the children
OL,18,Fthat we should not forget what that
OL,19,Fgeneration did for us, for our
OL,20,Ffreedom".
